01/09/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Authorities reported Sunday (31 August) that two fires were still raging in the Kljuc municipality. 
The state of emergency in the region remained in effect, though local officials said the situation has improved. 
Fire fighters have contained the blazes and hope to extinguish them by Monday at the latest. 
(BH Radio 1, BBC - 31/08/03)
